<A NAME="Original"></A>
<H2>Original Records</H2>

<P>For the <B>Bas-Rhin</B>, go to:
<A HREF="http://archives.bas-rhin.fr/registres-paroissiaux-et-documents-d-etat-civil/">
http://archives.bas-rhin.fr/registres-paroissiaux-et-documents-d-etat-civil/</A>,
then enter the town and select the year with the sliding bar.
</P>

<P>For the <B>Haut-Rhin</B>, go to:
<A HREF="http://www.archives.haut-rhin.fr">http://www.archives.haut-rhin.fr</A>.
</P>

<P>A few of the large towns, such as Strasbourg, have their own archives,
and some of the data were extracted from these on-line archives, mostly
in the years after 1902.
</P>

<P>In the actual record you should find the correct patronymic name,
possibly the names used before 1808, the parents’ name and their status
(living, in attendance, date of death), names of witnesses and their
relationship, sometimes dates and places of the banns.
</P>


